Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.70,0:01:37.75,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Connecting the points 
Dialogue: 2,0:01:39.47,0:01:42.77,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}哦，原来它存储了一个图片
Dialogue: 1,0:01:39.47,0:01:42.77,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}oh！it is an image
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.05,0:01:50.07,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}当我们给它上色后，就能拆分出三张红绿蓝通道的图片
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.05,0:01:50.07,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}When we color it, we can separate three RGB channel images.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.65,0:01:55.10,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这种像素化的图像也可以重新用矩阵存储起来
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.65,0:01:55.10,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}These pixelated images can also be stored back into a matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.10,0:02:01.27,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}矩阵的第二个身份是空间的建构师
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.10,0:02:01.27,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The second role of a matrix is the spatial architect.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:01.55,0:02:07.00,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}简单来说，一个矩阵的列向量通过线性组合，可以张成一个空间
Dialogue: 1,0:02:01.55,0:02:07.00,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Simply put, the column vectors of a matrix span a space through linear combinations.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.55,0:02:13.40,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}比如，对这样一个秩为2的矩阵就可以构建出整个二维空间
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.55,0:02:13.40,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}For example, a rank-2 matrix can construct a two-dimensional space.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:14.22,0:02:19.32,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们先写出这个矩阵的列向量的线性组合的数学表达
Dialogue: 1,0:02:14.22,0:02:19.32,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Let's first write the mathematical expression for the linear combinations of its column vectors.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:20.97,0:02:24.45,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}再在图上画出对应的这两个列向量
Dialogue: 1,0:02:20.97,0:02:24.45,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Then draw these two column vectors on the graph.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.57,0:02:30.87,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}将它们两个加起来，就得到了线性组合的图像化形式
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.57,0:02:30.87,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Adding them gives us the graphical form of the linear combination.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.32,0:02:35.65,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}调整列向量前的系数，就能得到不同的线性组合
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.32,0:02:35.65,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}By adjusting the coefficients, we can get different linear combinations.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.90,0:02:42.10,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这两个列向量的线性组合就可以像建构师一样构建出整个二维空间
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.90,0:02:42.10,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}These linear combinations can construct the entire two-dimensional space, just like an architect.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:47.42,0:02:49.97,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们再来构建三维空间
Dialogue: 1,0:02:47.42,0:02:49.97,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Let's move on to constructing a three-dimensional space.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.85,0:02:54.80,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们要构建三维空间，则需要一个秩为3的矩阵
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.85,0:02:54.80,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}To construct a 3D space, we need a rank-3 matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.02,0:03:01.77,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}同样，我们先写出三个列向量的线性组合
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.02,0:03:01.77,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Similarly, we first write the linear combinations of three column vectors.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.22,0:03:05.77,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后在图上画出他们三个列向量
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.22,0:03:05.77,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Then plot these three column vectors on the graph.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.37,0:03:11.52,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}将他们加起来得到线性组合
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.37,0:03:11.52,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Adding them together gives us the linear combination.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:14.97,0:03:17.70,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}如果我们调整每个向量前的系数
Dialogue: 1,0:03:14.97,0:03:17.70,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}By adjusting the coefficients for each vector,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:18.02,0:03:21.15,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}他们三个的线性组合，也就是这个绿色的箭头
Dialogue: 1,0:03:18.02,0:03:21.15,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}their linear combination, represented by this green arrow,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:21.32,0:03:23.82,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}就可以构建整个三维空间
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.32,0:03:23.82,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}can span the entire three-dimensional space.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:36.62,0:03:38.60,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们再来构建四维空间
Dialogue: 1,0:03:36.62,0:03:38.60,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Next, let's construct a four-dimensional space.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.92,0:03:41.77,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}此时我们需要一个秩为4的矩阵
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.92,0:03:41.77,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}This requires a rank-4 matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:47.90,0:03:54.77,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}同样先写出线性组合，并尝试在图上画出他们
Dialogue: 1,0:03:47.90,0:03:54.77,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Similarly, write the linear combinations and attempt to draw them.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.20,0:04:02.67,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但是在画第四个向量的时候，我们遇到了问题
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.20,0:04:02.67,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}However, we encounter a problem when plotting the fourth vector.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.07,0:04:08.37,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这个向量，它表示在第四维度上有一个单位长度，我们该怎么画呢？
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.07,0:04:08.37,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}This vector represents a unit length in the fourth dimension. How should we draw it?
