Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.77,0:05:06.67,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}We can imagine that each plane represents a 3D world.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.12,0:05:21.72,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}矩阵的第三个身份是线性变换魔法师
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.12,0:05:21.72,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The third role of a matrix is the wizard of linear transformations.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:22.92,0:05:24.82,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}第一种线性变换是旋转变换
Dialogue: 1,0:05:22.92,0:05:24.82,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The first type of linear transformation is rotation.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:25.12,0:05:27.37,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}它是旋转矩阵的独有的魔法
Dialogue: 1,0:05:25.12,0:05:27.37,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}It is the unique magic of rotation matrices.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:28.12,0:05:30.30,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}要成为旋转矩阵需要满足两个条件
Dialogue: 1,0:05:28.12,0:05:30.30,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}To become a rotation matrix, two conditions must be met.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:30.42,0:05:32.07,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}先成为正交矩阵
Dialogue: 1,0:05:30.42,0:05:32.07,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}First, it must be an orthogonal matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:32.37,0:05:34.50,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}其次是行列式为1
Dialogue: 1,0:05:32.37,0:05:34.50,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Second, its determinant must be 1.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:35.25,0:05:36.92,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这是它们的数学表达方式
Dialogue: 1,0:05:35.25,0:05:36.92,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}This is the mathematical expression.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:38.45,0:05:41.00,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们来看这个矩阵A
Dialogue: 1,0:05:38.45,0:05:41.00,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Let's look at this matrix A.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:41.07,0:05:43.02,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}它是不是旋转矩阵呢？
Dialogue: 1,0:05:41.07,0:05:43.02,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Is it a rotation matrix?
Dialogue: 2,0:05:43.07,0:05:45.70,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}先来算一下它满不满足第一个条件
Dialogue: 1,0:05:43.07,0:05:45.70,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}First, let's check if it meets the first condition.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:46.72,0:05:49.60,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}第一个条件要求A乘A转置为单位矩阵
Dialogue: 1,0:05:46.72,0:05:49.60,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The first condition requires A times A transpose to equal the identity matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:49.77,0:05:53.32,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}那么将A的行变为列就得到了A的转置
Dialogue: 1,0:05:49.77,0:05:53.32,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}So, by converting the rows of A into columns, we get its transpose.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:56.37,0:05:58.22,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}再计算矩阵乘法
Dialogue: 1,0:05:56.37,0:05:58.22,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Next, we compute the matrix multiplication.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:58.72,0:06:01.52,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这里我通过行列点积的方式进行计算
Dialogue: 1,0:05:58.72,0:06:01.52,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Here, I calculate it using the row-column dot product method.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:18.42,0:06:21.87,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}得到一个单位矩阵，第一个条件满足
Dialogue: 1,0:06:18.42,0:06:21.87,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The result is an identity matrix, so the first condition is satisfied.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.20,0:06:26.37,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}再来计算A的行列式，看他满不满足第二个条件
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.20,0:06:26.37,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Next, we calculate the determinant of A to see if it meets the second condition.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.75,0:06:29.75,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们沿着第三行展开行列式
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.75,0:06:29.75,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}We expand the determinant along the third row.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:37.95,0:06:40.77,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}前两项为0，来算第三项
Dialogue: 1,0:06:37.95,0:06:40.77,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The first two terms are zero; let's calculate the third term.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:41.02,0:06:43.87,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}主对角线相乘减副对角线
Dialogue: 1,0:06:41.02,0:06:43.87,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Multiply the main diagonal and subtract the secondary diagonal.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:48.02,0:06:53.30,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}最后得到1，满足了第二个条件，所以它是一个旋转矩阵
Dialogue: 1,0:06:48.02,0:06:53.30,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Finally, we get 1, satisfying the second condition. Therefore, it is a rotation matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:53.45,0:06:56.85,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但这个矩阵进行的是哪种类型旋转呢？
Dialogue: 1,0:06:53.45,0:06:56.85,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}But what type of rotation does this matrix perform?
Dialogue: 2,0:06:57.12,0:07:02.72,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我先剧透一下，它是对空间中的点，绕着z轴，旋转任意角度
Dialogue: 1,0:06:57.12,0:07:02.72,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Spoiler alert: It rotates points in space around the z-axis by any angle.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:04.97,0:07:08.97,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们可以对theta取任何值，比如取90度
Dialogue: 1,0:07:04.97,0:07:08.97,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}We can set theta to any value, for example, 90 degrees.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:09.12,0:07:10.90,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}就得到一个新的矩阵
Dialogue: 1,0:07:09.12,0:07:10.90,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}This gives us a new matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:11.10,0:07:15.25,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}取空间中任意一点的坐标，用矩阵左乘这个坐标
Dialogue: 1,0:07:11.10,0:07:15.25,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Take any point's coordinates in space and multiply them by this matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:15.45,0:07:17.67,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}就会得到结果坐标，我把它画在图上
Dialogue: 1,0:07:15.45,0:07:17.67,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}You'll get the resulting coordinates, which I plot on the graph.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:17.90,0:07:23.52,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}可以看到变换前后的夹角就正好是90度
Dialogue: 1,0:07:17.90,0:07:23.52,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}You can see that the angle between the original and transformed points is exactly 90 degrees.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:25.70,0:07:29.50,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}对一个点是这样，那么对许多点就都是这样
Dialogue: 1,0:07:25.70,0:07:29.50,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}This applies to one point and to many points as well.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.32,0:07:35.02,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}点构成线，线构成面
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.32,0:07:35.02,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Points form lines, and lines form planes.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.20,0:07:38.90,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}将矩阵作用于空间中的物体，比如这个篮球
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.20,0:07:38.90,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Apply the matrix to objects in space, such as this basketball.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:39.10,0:07:41.97,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}最终的效果就是将篮球旋转90度
Dialogue: 1,0:07:39.10,0:07:41.97,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The result is that the basketball is rotated by 90 degrees.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:49.62,0:07:52.87,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}再来看一种有意思的线性变换，投影
Dialogue: 1,0:07:49.62,0:07:52.87,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Now let's look at another interesting linear transformation: projection.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:53.07,0:07:56.00,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}投影变换是投影矩阵的特殊魔法
Dialogue: 1,0:07:53.07,0:07:56.00,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Projection transformation is the unique magic of projection matrices.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:56.32,0:08:00.22,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}投影矩阵需要满足这个条件：P平方等于P
Dialogue: 1,0:07:56.32,0:08:00.22,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Projection matrices must satisfy this condition: P^2 = P 
Dialogue: 2,0:08:00.42,0:08:07.07,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}也就是自身的平方还等于自己，因为投影两次的效果和投影一次是一样的
Dialogue: 1,0:08:00.42,0:08:07.07,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}This means squaring itself still equals itself, as projecting twice has the same effect as projecting once.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:07.32,0:08:08.82,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}举个例子
Dialogue: 1,0:08:07.32,0:08:08.82,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Here's an example.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:11.97,0:08:16.82,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}有这样一个矩阵P，我们复制一份，来算矩阵乘法
Dialogue: 1,0:08:11.97,0:08:16.82,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}We have this matrix P. Let's duplicate it and calculate the matrix multiplication.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:17.02,0:08:19.02,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}看它满不满足条件
Dialogue: 1,0:08:17.02,0:08:19.02,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Let's see if it satisfies the condition.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:19.27,0:08:23.47,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这里我换一种矩阵乘法的计算方式，按列计算
Dialogue: 1,0:08:19.27,0:08:23.47,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Here, I use a column-by-column calculation method.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:23.67,0:08:26.62,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}效果和之前行列点积是一样的
Dialogue: 1,0:08:23.67,0:08:26.62,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The result is the same as the row-column dot product method.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:26.80,0:08:31.65,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你还记得这个运算规则吗？
Dialogue: 1,0:08:26.80,0:08:31.65,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Do you remember this computation rule?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:35.77,0:08:39.47,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}算出结果，确实和原本的矩阵P一致
Dialogue: 1,0:08:35.77,0:08:39.47,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}The result matches the original matrix P.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:39.70,0:08:41.82,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}所以它确实是一个投影矩阵
Dialogue: 1,0:08:39.70,0:08:41.82,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}So it is indeed a projection matrix.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:42.07,0:08:45.05,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}它会有什么投影效果呢？我们来分析一下
Dialogue: 1,0:08:42.07,0:08:45.05,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}What projection effect does it have? Let's analyze it.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:45.65,0:08:50.27,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}给空间中任意一点x，y，z，左乘投影矩阵，算出结果
Dialogue: 1,0:08:45.65,0:08:50.27,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Take any point (x, y, z) in space, multiply it by the projection matrix, and calculate the result.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:50.65,0:08:55.37,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们发现，这个点的x，y分量没有变，只有z分量归0了
Dialogue: 1,0:08:50.65,0:08:55.37,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}We find that the x and y components remain unchanged, while the z component becomes zero.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:55.57,0:08:57.85,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你能想象到它是什么效果吗？
Dialogue: 1,0:08:55.57,0:08:57.85,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Can you imagine what this effect is?
Dialogue: 2,0:08:57.95,0:09:02.07,123,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们将视角放在宇宙空间，来欣赏一下它的效果
Dialogue: 1,0:08:57.95,0:09:02.07,Default-L2,atg6,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Let's switch our perspective to outer space to appreciate its effect.